The article discusses the economic relationship between the United States and India. It highlights India as an important emerging market with a growing GDP and a large consumer market. The US government is taking steps to expand exports to India through advocacy, trade finance, and dialogue with the Indian government. US merchandise exports to India have quadrupled since 2002, reaching $16.4 billion. Top export categories include machinery, aircraft and parts, electric machinery, and fertilizers. Various states in the US benefit from exports to India, with California, Texas, Washington, New York, and Florida being the largest state exporters. US services exports to India have also seen significant growth, with the travel sector, education services, and business and professional services being the major categories.